133 (..../Day8$ cut -f3 Day8.transcripts.gtf.tmap | sort | uniq -c | grep c -> lalu cek manual berapa nilai c)
26. How many cufflinks transcripts are partial reconstructions of reference transcripts (‘contained’)? (Day16)
21 (..../Day16$ cut -f3 Day16.transcripts.gtf.tmap | sort | uniq -c | grep c -> lalu cek manual berapa nilai c)
27. How many cufflinks transcripts are novel splice variants of reference genes? (Day8)
14 (..../Day8$ cut -f3 Day8.transcripts.gtf.tmap | sort | uniq -c | grep j -> lalu cek manual berapa nilai j)
28. How many cufflinks transcripts are novel splice variants of reference genes? (Day16)
22 (..../Day16$ cut -f3 Day16.transcripts.gtf.tmap | sort | uniq -c | grep j -> lalu cek manual berapa nilai j)
29. How many cufflinks transcripts were formed in the introns of reference genes? (Day8)
4 (..../Day8$ cut -f3 Day8.transcripts.gtf.tmap | sort | uniq -c | grep i -> lalu cek manual berapa nilai i)
